info.name: USPTO Trademark Search API
info.description:
The [USPTO Trademark API](https://rapidapi.com/pentium10/api/uspto-trademark) hosted on RapidAPI Hub provides access to the USPTO Trademark Search API, offering instant trademark search, availability checks, and comprehensive data retrieval from the United States Patent and Trademark Office. It includes endpoints for keyword searches, serial number lookups, owner information, and database status, with support for batch processing and pagination where applicable.

**Key Features:**

- Keyword Search (generic and full text)
    
- Trademark Availability Check
    
- Expiring Trademarks by Date
    
- Trademarks by Registration Date
    
- Serial Number Search (detailed info)
    
- Owner Search
    
- Batch Processing for efficient data retrieval (up to 25,000 results for batch calls)
    
- Pagination Support for large result sets
    
- Database Status (freshness, latest updates, updated daily)
    
- Check out [FAQ](https://rapidapi.com/pentium10/api/uspto-trademark/tutorials/faq-)
    

**Authentication:**  
This API uses **RapidAPI's API Key authentication**. You will need to set your `X-RapidAPI-Key` in the collection variables. To get the API key subscribe to packages [here](https://rapidapi.com/pentium10/api/uspto-trademark).

urlencoded.description: A JSON array string of keywords to search for (e.g., ["keyword1","keyword2"]). Max 100 keywords, each > 3 chars.
Set to 0 for the initial call to start from the beginning. For subsequent pagination calls, use `next_index` from the previous response.

request.description: Runs a keyword search on an array of keywords. This is the **initial call** that consumes credits (equal to number of keywords) and returns a `scroll_id` and pagination details, but no results. Use the 'Batch Trademark Search - Pagination Call' to retrieve results.

urlencoded.description: A JSON array string of keywords. Must be the same as the initial call's keywords.
Use the `next_index` value from the previous API response to paginate through results. Max 250 results per page.
The `scroll_id` obtained from the initial call. Valid for ~1 hour.

request.description: Retrieves paginated results for a batch keyword search. This call consumes 0 credits. The `scroll_id` and `keywords` must match the initial call, and `start_index` should be set to `next_index` from the previous response.
